{
  "texts": [
    "Noteworthy CNN architectures, including VGGNet, 123CaffeNet, GoogleNet, and ResNet, have demonstrated their efficacy.",
    "Despite their success, challenges persist, as CNNs often focus on extracting global features, neglecting crucial object information within images.To bridge this gap, we propose the Residual Channel-attention network (RCA), a novel method that integrates a lightweight residual network for spatial feature extraction and a channel attention mechanism to emphasize important feature channels selectively.",
    "The incorporation of a squeeze-and-excitation network as a self-attention mechanism enables a focus on the most informative features related to remote sensing images, disregarding irrelevant information.",
    "In summary, this study provides the following four main contributions:• We propose a self-attention deep network structure for image scene classifications based on remote sensing that incorporates the channel-attention mechanism into the residual convolutional network.",
    "The self-attention mechanism drives the network to focus on the most critical parts of images while suppressing background disturbance."
  ]
}